description:
We are looking for a Presales Consultant to join our EMEA team!




* Are you passionate about demonstrating the effectiveness of our innovative products to prospective customers?
We are seeking an individual with the ability to identify critical business challenges and seamlessly adapt our software to deliver tailored, effective solutions.  



Who we are:

SAI360 is giving companies a new perspective on risk management. By integrating Governance, Risk, Compliance (GRC) software and Ethics & Compliance Learning resources, SAI360 can broaden your risk horizon and increase your ability to identify, manage, and mitigate risk. See risk from every angle. Visit www.sai360.com .



Think you’re a fit for SAI360?

As a Presales Consultant, you will be responsible for working with prospective customers to understand their business requirements and identify how these can be met by SAI360 software solutions. You will prepare/conduct product presentations and demonstrations, effectively representing the software capabilities and their relevance to the potential client’s key objectives, whilst answering RFP’s from a functional point of view. In addition, you will feed back your observations from the market to SAI360’s product management and product marketing teams.



The primary objectives and responsibilities of a Presales Consultant includes:




Pre-Sales (Solution Consulting)


* Understand customer needs and map them to SAI360 capabilities;
* Deliver tailored product demos and respond to RFPs;
* Document business requirements and configure the software for demonstrations;
* Provide market feedback to product and marketing teams;
* Support multiple sales campaigns and ensure smooth handover to implementation

teams.

Post-Sales (Customer Success)


* Define success criteria and track progress with the Account Manager;
* Plan and support solution roll-out, training, and user adoption;
* Manage reporting needs and custom configurations;
* Act as an escalation point for product issues and coordinate resolutions;
* Share product roadmap updates and align them with customer goals;
* Drive customer satisfaction, retention, and account growth.

Professional Services


* Design & Configure: Gather requirements, document functional designs, and configure

the SAI360 GRC solution;


* Project Execution: Support the customer team, resolve UAT issues, and deliver training;
* Quality & Reporting: Ensure project quality, flag risks or changes, and provide weekly

updates to the Project Manager.



What you’ll bring to the table:

* Proven track record of experience conducting customer needs analysis and product demonstrations, within a 6-12 month sales cycle;
* Experience selling into highly regulated industries is desirable;
* An understanding of Governance, Risk and Compliance solutions is critical to success;
* Must be able to use Microsoft Office products and Salesforce.com;
* Experience with Microsoft PowerBI is highly advantageous;
* Excellent interpersonal, written and verbal communication skills and presentation skills required;
* Needs to be able to grasp and smoothly articulate the challenges involved in complying with key risk and regulatory requirements for target industries, establishing and implementing enterprise risk and compliance strategies, and how customers can more effectively manage compliance with changing laws and regulations;
* Ability to solve complex problems with a solutions-oriented focus;
* Highly organised and detail-oriented, able to perform in a fast-paced environment;
* Ability to work independently and as part of a virtual team with open, collaborative communication;
Full commitment to conduct business with the utmost integrity and in full compliance with the law is absolutely essential.  



Why you should apply to SAI360:

Alongside a remote-first hiring strategy and competitive salary package, we offer a wide variety of employee perks including –

* 20 days annual leave;
* Quarterly wellness days;
* Bonus incentive Plan;
* EAP access;
* CPF;
* Life assurance;
* Private medical;
